OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry with variable
OL,6,Famounts of cloud and some bright or
OL,7,Fsunny spells. A few showers may break
OL,8,Fout, this mainly across the south.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FAny showers slowly dying out
OL,11,Fthis evening. Then the rest of the
OL,12,Fnight will be dry with variable
OL,13,Famounts of cloud. A cold night with
OL,14,Fpatchy frost.
OL,15,
OL,16,CSunday:FAfter a cold start the morning
OL,17,Fwill be dry and bright. Staying dry in
OL,18,Fthe afternoon but clouding over.
OL,19,FPatchy rain spreading south in the
OL,20,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
